    1 KOOL WhatsApp Notifications Enhance customer communication by notifying them about every business activity via WhatsApp with KOOL WhatsApp Notifications, which allows admins to send multiple messages to customers easily. MageCompʼs KOOL WhatsApp Notifications app uses the Official WhatsApp Business API, allowing Shopify admins to send notifications to their customers about their order statuses, such as order confirmation, refund, order delivery, order out for delivery, abandoned cart etc. This app is the best solution for increasing customer satisfaction and brand loyalty. Admins can also send bulk and broadcast messages to their customers to promote their promo offers, store events, discounts, store sales, new product arrivals, etc. 2 General Settings To start using the app for your Shopify store, you need enable the app status and proceed. If you do not want to send messages for POS Orders, then you can disable the field. To activate the WhatsApp Chat button, you need to select the Activate WhatsApp Button. App Status Activate the WhatsApp Chat Button 3 After selecting the button, you will be redirected to your store's theme backend where you need to enable the app embed. 4 In order to configure it, you just need to enter your Access Token so that you can send notifications via WhatsApp to your customers. Once you've entered the access token, click Save button & you're done. Enter the contact number on which you want to receive notifications and updates on customer activities. Settings Admin Notification Contact Detail 5 6 Notification Templates From this Shopify app's backend section, you can easily customize the messages and notifications for sending out to your customers. 1.Customer Notifications 2.Admin Notifications 7 Customer Notifications With this Shopify app, you can send multiple types of notifications to your customers. This notification will be sent to your customers automatically after they've placed the order. • Message Field: Enter the WhatsApp message that you want to send to your customers. You can incorporate variables in the message to make it dynamic. Order Place 8 Variables • {%-order_id-%} • {%-customer_name-%} • {%-shop_email-%} • {%-shop_domain-%} • {%-order_status_page-%} • {%-order_items-%} • {%-order_value-%} • {%-shipping_address-%} As we've included every variable possible in the message template, it will enhance your brand impression as it will give your customers a chance to review their details once again. The above draft message would look like below when delivered to the customer. "Dear, John Matt Your order 12345 of $499 with a Nike Crackle Print TB Tee and Nike Swoosh Pro Flat Peak Cap has been placed successfully. You will get the order tracking information as we ship your order to 1652 Waldeck Street, Cleburne, TX 76031. You can check your order status at https://www.xyzstore.com/order-status. Thank you for shopping with
    
